The paper deals with multiagent systems and learning optimal actions in the presence of latent policies or types. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) for the learning aspect, Game Theory (cs.GT) for the coordination aspect, and Machine Learning (cs.LG) for the algorithmic aspect. Additionally, the paper deals with multiagent systems (cs.MA) and the convergence properties of the learning algorithm, which could fall under Systems and Control (cs.SY).
